div3.p:
He was born at Limerick, Ireland, in 1825; received the habit, November 21st, 1852;
							profession, August 15th, 1853. He attended Michigan City, from March 1855 to December
							1856. He died, September 23, 1886, and is buried at Notre Dame.

He was born at Unter-Muensterthal, diocese of Freiburg, Germany, August 20, 1821;
							came to this country, May 12, 1847; ordained priest at Peru, Ohio, June 5, 1849. He
							was pastor of St. Mary's Church, Decatur, from June 1857 till May 1858.

He was born at Urach, Black Forests, Archdiocese of Freiburg, Germany, May 12, 1856;
							came to America, October 15, 1876; ordained priest, May 28, 1885. He attended Portland
							as a mission, from March to July 1904.

He was born in 1820, at Ems, Switzerland; came to this country in December 1850;
							ordained priest, by Bishop Rappe of Cleveland, at Tiffin, Ohio, January 27, 1851;
							entered the Congregation of the Most Precious Blood in Switzerland. He was the founder
							of the mission house, convent and parish of Holy Trinity, Jay county, in 1853. He died
							December 15, 1854 and is buried at St. Mary's Home.
